In England, in the seven days to 10 March, there were 306,556 new confirmed cases (542.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 March, there were 187,554 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 63% (119,002 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 15 March is 16,709,007 (29,547.2 cases per 100,000 population).
